=============================================================================================================
Notes:

MacOS X: 
  The provided universal binary QuantumKernelX (the MathLink executable) has been compiled on 64 bit

Linux:
  The provided Makefiles have been tested on 64 bit Linux.

Windows: 
  tested on Windows 10.
  For compiling you need to install a GNU compiler and tools, e.g., cygwin from http://www.cygwin.com , 
  including g++ and  make .
  It is recommended to install cygwin to C:\cygwin

=============================================================================================================

Building the executables on Mathematica 11 from this directory:

Run from a terminal (shell):

MacOS X univerisal binary :
make -f Makefile.macosx clean;  make -f Makefile.macosx

Linux 64 bit:
make -f Makefile.linux clean;  make -f Makefile.linux; mv QuantuKernel ..; make -f Makefile.linux clean

Windows 64 bit:
make -f Makefile.windows clean; make -f Makefile.windows ; mv QuantumKernel.exe .. ; make -f Makefile.windows clean

================================================================================================================
Then copy the resulting Mathlink executable, i.e., QuantumKernel, QuantumKernelX, QuantumKernel32 or QuantumKernel64
to the VQM package directory, i.e., to the parent directory of this Source directory.


